JS*******************************************
//we set a new variable counter to our html paragraph counter. we then set a variable x to 0 so our counter knows where to start from. And 
like I stated before, myCounter variable is set to setInterval. inside of the setInterval parameter area, notice the word function, 
without this, we would not be able to use the onclick method in html. we then set x to increment by 1 every second or 1000 milaseconds.
var counter = document.getElementById("counter");
var x = 0;
var myCounter = setInterval(function(){x++; counter.innerHTML = x},1000 );
